In re the Matter of BENTON COUNTY SEWER DISTRICT NO. 1 OF BENTON COUNTY, Missouri, Appellant,
v.
George HALL, Respondent; Josephine Baker, Respondent. WD 81510 Missouri Court of Appeals, Western District. ORDER FILED: January 8, 2019
Motion for Rehearing and/or Transfer to Supreme Court Denied February 26, 2019 Charles E. Weedman, Jr., Harrisonville, MO, for appellant. David J. Moen, Jefferson City, MO, for respondent Josephine Baker. George M. Hall, respondent pro se. Before Division Three: Gary D. Witt, Presiding Judge, Cynthia L. Martin, Judge and Anthony Rex Gabbert, Judge

ORDER

Per curiam:

Appellant Benton County Sewer Dist. No. 1 of Benton County, Missouri ("District"), appeals the judgment of the circuit court of Benton County, Missouri, vacating its order appointing a receiver for the District. The District raises two allegations of error in the court's judgment. For reasons explained more fully in a memorandum provided to the parties, we affirm. Rule 84.16(b).
